data.title: King Fouad II Releases New Photo with Grandchildren
data.meta_description: King Fouad II Releases New Photo with Grandchildren
data.text:
King Fouad II released a new photo with his daughter-in-law Princess Noal Zaher and his two grandchildren Prince Fouad Zaher and Princess Farah Noor on Monday.

Arabian Royal Agency, an online platform specializing in Arabian royal new, wrote on Twitter: “New Photo Exclusive to RoyalAgency Egypt’s Last King Fouad II With His daughter-in-law Princess Noal Zaher and his grandchildren Prince Fouad Zaher Hassan and Princess Farah Noor.”

https://twitter.com/ARoyalAgency/status/1122828606114336769

King Fouad II

King Ahmed Fouad II is a member of the Egyptian Muhammad Ali dynasty. He was the last king of Egypt and Sudan from July 1952 to June 1953.

Fouad II was born on January 16, 1952, and he ascended the throne on July 26, 1952. He is the son of King Farouk and his wife Queen Narriman. After the Egyptian revolution in 1952, He left with his family to Italy.

In 1976, he married Dominique-France Loeb Picard, who converted from Judaism to Islam and was given the Arabic name Fadila. Although this marriage did not last too long, she gave birth to three children, two princes, Muhammad Ali and Fakhruddin, and one princess, Fawzia. After they porced, King Fouad II moved from France to Switzerland.

[caption id="attachment_48288" align="aligncenter" width="901"] Fouad's Daughter-in-law Noal Zaher[/caption]
